<font color="#FF0000">CHRISTMAS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Dec 15 18:57:29 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I saw Bob Hope on Christmas &quot;66.&quot;  He said that he heard Vietnam looks beautiful from the sky -- on a Pan Am flight going out.  He brought Phyliss Diller and Joey Heatherton with him.  I stood in the back of thousands of other troops in Cu Chi.<br><br>
I was home a week on Christmas &quot;67.&quot;  I participated in the end of a friendship with my &quot;alter ego.&quot;<br><br>
This Christmas should be fun.  My daughter and I will decorate the tree on Christmas eve and shake a few presents under the tree.  Some traditions are worth their weight in gold.<br><br>
Paul
